description: As the sun set Monday, the looting started once again across Manhattan as protests entered their fifth day in New York City.Businesses on 5th and Madison avenues were spotted putting up plywood to prevent looting. However, that didn't stop the looters from breaking in and grabbing what they wanted from the luxury stores.NYPD officers were standing by shops with shattered windows like the The Nintendo Store, Michael Kors, Kate Spade and Barnes and Noble. title: Making History: NASA and SpaceX Launch Astronauts to Space! (#LaunchAmerica Success May 30, 2020)
description: Watch history unfold on Saturday, May 30, as NASA and SpaceX launch astronauts Robert Behnken and Douglas Hurley to the International Space Station. This mission marks the first time since the retirement of the space shuttle in 2011 that humans will fly to the space station from U.S. soil. The mission's first launch attempt on Wednesday, May 27 was scrubbed due to weather conditions.Â Tune in starting at 11 a.m. EDT as NASA and SpaceX provide joint, live coverage from launch to arrival at the space station. Teams are targeting 3:22 p.m. EDT for the launch of the SpaceX Crew Dragon spacecraft atop a Falcon 9 rocket from historic Launch Complex 39A at NASAâ€™s Kennedy Space Center in Florida. The Crew Dragon is scheduled to dock to the space station on Sunday, May 31.Learn more about the mission: https://www.nasa.gov/launchamerica/Chats are moderated. description: So I am a huge fan of fancy soaps, in every way, shape, and form - I love smelling soaps, feeling soaps, and using soaps - and last year I even tried following a soap art tutorial to attempt to make my own batch of snazzy, swirly soap. So when I stumbled upon a whole new category of soapy treats - *dessert* soaps - I figured, we had to try and make some soap cupcakes for ourselves. So I followed a sparkling champagne soap cupcake tutorial from Soap Queen TV/Bramble Berry with ~interesting~ results, to say the least!EDIT: also, apparently the goggles we were wearing aren't the safest option, so if you try something like this please get some real soap-making goggles!!This video is NOT sponsored!!Safiya's Instagram: https://www.instagram.com/safiyany/Twitter: https://twitter.com/safiyajnFacebook: https://www.facebook.com/safnygaard/The tutorial we followed is here: https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=qwnm0gpJk2MYou can check out Anne Marie's channel here: https://www.youtube.com/user/soapqueentvAnd the Soap Queen blog here: https://www.soapqueen.com/And the Brambleberry store here: https://www.brambleberry.com/And the inspo for this video, Nectar Bath Treats here:https://www.instagram.com/nectarbathtreats/?hl=enMUSICVia AudioNetwork

After 30 Years I Am Still 17
description: My name is Amara and I am 17 years old. But I seem to be the only one who believes that. Donâ€™t get confused just yet! Iâ€™ll tell you everything and Iâ€™m sure youâ€™ll agree with me too. Before I do that though, click subscribe and like this video - I might just appear in your dreams tonight if you donâ€™t. Ok, letâ€™s go.I remember that I was 15 when my parents relocated to America from India. My dad was quite rich so we were living in the richest neighbourhood in the city and I was attending the most expensive high school too. My parents gave me and my little sister everything we wanted but my little sister got more because she was my dadâ€™s favorite. I was three years older but she was smarter. I envied her when she got all the praises but I was more interested in partying and shopping with my friends. One time, I was ata party when I had an exam and my dad called me and said, â€œIf you donâ€™t do well in school. Iâ€™ll not include you in my will.â€ Letâ€™s just say I failed so bad that I had to change schools.My new school was cooler than the first. There were hotter boys and sassier girls. If I did not come from a rich home, I would have felt like a loser but I got along just fine. I didnâ€™t tell you Iâ€™m a great dancer, right? Well, Iâ€™m such a badass that I became the captain of the cheerleading squad. I know I already said the boys at this school are super-hot but if thereâ€™s a word that can be used to describe someone who is way hotter, then you can insert it here for Greg, the captain of the basketball team. We started dating after he walked up to me one day and was like, â€œHey, I love your birthmark and youâ€™re really cute. Wanna hang out sometime?â€ That was the beginning and end of that.Everything might have seemed perfect with me but as an Indian, it was hard for me to pronounce some English words correctly. I once pronounced â€˜Bicycleâ€™ at my former school as â€˜bai-siiklâ€™ and it made everyone laugh and make fun of me for about a week. I started taking special English classes but to avoid embarrassment at my new school, I just stuck with words I was confident of pronouncing or pointed to things I wanted to talk about. At first, my friends thought I was weird but they got used to it. But I was quite comfortable with Greg, so I didnâ€™t mind making those mistakes around him as he seemed like he didnâ€™t care about it.Greg and I spent a lot of time going to the movies, arcades and live concerts. We were almost inseparable., youcanâ€™t see me anywhere and not find him close by or something. We were the perfect couple and everyone wanted their relationship to be like ours. Once while we were hanging out, I told him that I would like to live with him on a remote island and have twins with him. The thought of a life without Greg in it always made me cringe! Then a new girl showed up.Her name was Lucy and she was very pretty. You can call it jealousy but on her first day of school, everyone in class was like, â€œOooh, sheâ€™s so hot!â€ and it made me uncomfortable. Oneday, she came up to me and said, â€œHi Amara, I heard youâ€™re the cheerleading captain, when can I come for tryouts?â€ I wanted to tell her that we werenâ€™t open to new intakes but I saw a chance to make life a bit miserable for her and I took it.

description: The NYPD changed tactics during a tamer night of protests Wednesday, breaking up peaceful demonstrations after the curfew had passed, angering some elected officials.Advocates credited the new approach with stopping some of the destruction of previous nights, but critics said the calm came at a high price as the city was forced to grind to a halt at 8 p.m.Bridges were closed to traffic, and police arrested dozens of orderly people for violating the curfew. About an hour after the deadline to get off the street, officers began moving in on crowds of demonstrators in Manhattan and Brooklyn, at times blasting people with pepper spray or using batons to shove people who didn't move fast enough.Two large peaceful protests that continued after the curfew were broken up by police, resulting in 180 arrests in both Downtown Brooklyn and on the Upper East Side.More details: https://7ny.tv/3eSrcvv----Check out more Eyewitness News - http://7ny.tv/2suJHTdNEW HERE? â€“ Hi! title: It's Time to Take our Singapore Jobs Back! Lim Tean's Budget Response
tags: Lim Tean|Peoples Voice|Singapore politics|PAP singapore|singapore opposition politics|Singapore covid|employment singapore|jobs singapore|singapore peoples voice
description: The Singapore General Elections are looming and the latest budget delivered a couple of days ago show the PAP desperately juggling their need to sweeten the ground they have soured as well as patching up their rear-view mirror response to Covid-19.After acting so late to the Pandemic and thus causing Singapore to endure an extended lock-down, they are now having to dig deep into our reserves to stabilise the economy.In this video, Party Leader of Peoples Voice Lim Tean responds to the budget, on how the figures don't quite add up, a large bulk is being held in 'contingency' and there are no fresh or new ideas about how to stimulate the economy. More importantly Singaporeans are cash-strapped, after only receiving a one-time $600 payout back in April, Lim Tean advises that a second payout of $1,000 is given to each citizen. This would still be less than other countries in our region and beyond but would go a long way to alleviate the extraordinary hardship people are experiencing.Lim Tean also touches upon the Peoples Party manifesto point of freezing all S-passes for a time and dramatically reducing the amount of employment passes offered to foreigners.  It is time to take back our jobs! No decent govt will allow job opportunities to go to a foreigner ahead of it's own citizens.In order to stimulate our economy we need to get our people back to work, back to the jobs that exist in our country and not hand them over to the lowest bidder.www.PeoplesPartySg.com

title: President Trump widely condemned over handling of US protests - BBC News
tags: bbc|bbc news|news|President|Trump|protests|unrest|United States|US|condemnation|George Floyd|cities|murder|killing|police|officers|black|military|Joe Biden|White House|Democrats|Minneapolis|Huw Edwards|Aleem Maqbool|Barbara Plett Usher|correspondent|Washington|violence|Will Gompertz|Spike Lee|Arts|Editor|Jon Sopel|North America
description: President Trump is facing widespread condemnation for his handling of the unrest in dozens of American cities. It follows the killing of George Floyd, an African-American man who died last week in Minneapolis while being detained by police. His death has now been declared a homicide following an official post-mortem.There's been more violence and looting in some US cities prompting Mr Trump to say he would send in the military. The president's Democratic rival for the White House, Joe Biden, accused Mr Trump of using racist language and failing in his presidential duty to unite the nation. The film director Spike Lee, in an interview with the BBC, described President Trump as a gangster who was inflaming racial divisions that had existed since the foundation of the United States and its history of slavery. Huw Edwards presents BBC News at Ten reporting from Aleem Maqbool at the White House,  Barbara Plett Usher in Minneapolis, Arts Editor Will Gompertz speaking to Spike Lee, and North America Editor Jon Sopel. description: What protest news coverage does â€”Â and doesn't â€”Â show you.Become a Video Lab member! http://bit.ly/video-labThe killings of George Floyd, Breonna Taylor, and Ahmaud Arbery have ignited protests around the world. Those protests have dominated news coverage. But when it comes to communicating the protestsâ€™ scale, character, and purpose, a lot of that coverage falls short.Part of that is because of the mediaâ€™s incentive to highlight the most dramatic imagery; itâ€™s why so much protest coverage has been filled with violent and chaotic scenes of fire, looters, and tear gas. But itâ€™s also because of the nature of protest imagery itself. In this video, journalism professor Jason Johnson and Vox editor Kainaz Amaria explain that, while the news can show you what a protest looks like, itâ€™s a lot worse at telling you why itâ€™s happening.Further reading: https://www.vox.com/first-person/2020/5/29/21274891/george-floyd-cop-arrested-minneapolis-breonna-taylorVox.com is a news website that helps you cut through the noise and understand what's really driving the events in the headlines. description: Â» Subscribe to NowThis: http://go.nowth.is/News_SubscribeÂ» Sign up for our newsletter KnowThis to get the biggest stories of the day delivered straight to your inbox: https://go.nowth.is/KnowThisIn World news and current events today, world leaders from around the globe have condemned President Donald Trump and his response to the peaceful protest happening in front of the White House as a result of the police killing of George Floyd. The senseless act has sparked a movement of George Floyd protests and Black Lives Matter protests not just in America, but around the world, but no other leader has responded to the uprising with the same violent rhetoric as President Trump. From Prime Minister Justin Trudeau of Canada to UK Prime Minister Boris Johnson of England, international leaders from Germany to the entire European Union have roundly condemned the violent response of Donald J. title: Making History: NASA and SpaceX Launch Astronauts to Space! (#LaunchAmerica Attempt May 27, 2020)
description: Recorded May 27, 2020: Watch history unfold on Wednesday, May 27, as NASA and SpaceX launch astronauts Robert Behnken and Douglas Hurley to the International Space Station. This mission marks the first time since the retirement of the space shuttle in 2011 that humans will fly to the space station from U.S. soil. Tune in starting at 12:15 p.m. EDT as NASA and SpaceX provide joint, live coverage from launch to arrival at the space station. Teams are targeting 4:33 p.m. EDT for the launch of the SpaceX Crew Dragon spacecraft atop a Falcon 9 rocket from historic Launch Complex 39A at NASAâ€™s Kennedy Space Center in Florida. The Crew Dragon is scheduled to dock to the space station at 11:29 a.m. Thursday, May 28.Learn more about the mission: https://www.nasa.gov/launchamerica/Chats are moderated. description: Seorang pelakon drama dihadapkan ke Mahkamah Majistret Ampang pada Jumaat, 29 Mei, atas dakwaan memikat isteri orang dan mengajak melakukan persetubuhan.Muhammad Shah Radhi Hazvee, 24, atau dikenali dengan nama pentas Shah Hazvee, memakai baju T berbelang kelabu hitam dan seluar khakis, mengaku tidak bersalah selepas tuduhan dibacakan terhadapnya di hadapan Majistret Farah Nasihah Annuar.Mengikut tuduhan, pelakon drama 'Monalisa' dan 'Hero' itu didakwa memikat isteri orang berusia 36 tahun dan supaya wanita itu melakukan persetubuhan dengannya.Muhammad Shah Radhi didakwa mengikut Seksyen 498 Kanun Keseksaan yang membawa hukuman maksimum penjara dua tahun atau denda atau kedua-duanya sekali jika sabit kesalahan.-------------------------------------#HMETRO #METROTVPlease visit our website for more news http://www.hmetro.com.myPlease like http://www.facebook.com/harianmetro Please follow http://www.twitter.com/hmetromyAnd also our http://www.instagram.com/hmetromy

title: Could China-India border dispute trigger a military conflict? I Inside Story
tags: dispute|politics|al jazeera|china news|aljazeera|asia news|aljazeera english|al jazeera english|india|inside story|aljazeera news|trade|china|military|aljazeera live|india news|conflict
description: Trouble is brewing at the roof of the world.India and China both claim territory along the Himalayas.Their border dispute goes back decades.The Indian military says in the first week of May, Indian and Chinese soldiers scuffled and threw stones at each other in the Pangong Tso lake and Naku La areas.Chinese state media say Indian troops trespassed on Chinese territory, but India's government said its soldiers stayed on its side. Satellite images appear to show both sides bolstering their presence along the Line of Actual Control separating the two armies.So why is this happening now?Presenter: Bernard SmithGuests:Brahma Chellaney - Professor of Strategic Studies at the Center for Policy Research, and a former Adviser to India's National Security Council.
